## 6️⃣ Server-Sent Events (SSE) — Simpler One-Way Streaming

For one-directional updates (notifications, live feeds), SSE is simpler than WebSockets:

```javascript
// Express SSE endpoint
app.get('/api/notifications/live', requireAuth, (req, res) => {
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream')
  res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache')
  res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive')

  const send = (data) => res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(data)}

`)

  const interval = setInterval(() => {
    send({ type: 'ping', time: new Date() })
  }, 30000)

  req.on('close', () => clearInterval(interval))  // Client disconnected
})

// React client
const source = new EventSource('/api/notifications/live')
source.onmessage = (e) => {
  const notification = JSON.parse(e.data)
  addNotification(notification)
}
```

