## 7️⃣ Debouncing API Calls

For search inputs, debounce to avoid an API call on every keystroke:

```javascript
function SearchInput() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState("")
  const [results, setResults] = useState([])

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!query) { setResults([]); return }

    const timer = setTimeout(async () => {
      const { data } = await api.get(`/api/search?q=${query}`)
      setResults(data)
    }, 300)  // Wait 300ms after last keystroke

    return () => clearTimeout(timer)  // Cancel if user types again
  }, [query])

  return <input value={query} onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
}
```

---

## 💡 Summary

| Concept | Use When |
|---|---|
| Optimistic UI | User actions where failure is rare (likes, toggles) |
| Rollback | Server rejects the optimistic change |
| React Query `onMutate` | Cleanest optimistic pattern |
| WebSockets | Chat, collaborative editing, live notifications |
| SSE | One-way live data streams (feeds, notifications) |
| Debouncing | Search inputs, autocomplete |
